Description: Ibanez Artcore AG86-TRD 12-01 ________________________________ You are looking at an Ibanez Artcore, full hollow body AG86-TRD-12-01 Guitar, also known as Expressionist. it has a slightly smaller body than the AF models for effortless performance characteristics, while maintaining the excellent sound quality of the full hollow body. Built in June of 2002, it is finished in high gloss transparent red over figured Bubinga (African Rosewood) with a matching solid figured Bubinga pick guard as well as the optional Ibanez DX inlay, which is a combination of abalone/mother of pearl precision block inlay position markers, the inlay on the closed trapeze, and the specialized headstock inlay. It has been professionally set-up with D'Addario ECG 24, Jazz Light, flat wound chromes (.011 to .050), which includes a wound G, the Art 1 floating bridge, with tuning (TOM type) saddle, and closed trapeze tailpiece, make for effortless string changing, and maintenance of proper string length tuning. It has absolutely unbelievable tone quality with exceptional intonation, and easy on the fingers low action. As you can see from the photos, it is a beautiful guitar, with just some negligible scuffs from normal use. Features: Artcore 3pc. Maple/ Mahogany Set-In neck with Bound Rosewood Fret Board Figured Bubinga (African Rosewood) top/sides/back Body with matching solid figured Bubinga pick guard Transparent Red finish 22 medium frets Art 1 bridge with tuning (Tune-O-Matic type) saddle ACH1 (Humbucker) Neck PU ACH2 (Humbucker) Bridge PU Artcore DX Inlay Chrome Hardware It comes with an original Ibanez black plush lined, hard shell case, by TKL, which is in very good condition. This instrument would be great for a player of any level. Shipping charge is the actual cost to your zip code.
